└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ 2.5.4 API KEY SECURITY                                          │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ Scanned for exposed keys:                                       │
│ □ API_KEY/SECRET in src/: [N found / none]                     │
│ □ Private keys in frontend: [list or "none"]                   │
│                                                                 │
│ Security issues:                                                │
│ - [file]: [key type] exposed → MOVE TO EDGE FUNCTION           │
│ - [none found]                                                  │
│                                                                 │
│ VERDICT: [SECURE / FIX REQUIRED - add to plan]                 │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ 2.5.5 SEMANTIC DUPLICATE DETECTION                              │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ Scope: files listed in this phase's Files section only          │
│                                                                 │
│ For each file, read exported functions and look for pairs that  │
│ perform similar operations through different approaches:        │
│ □ Same API calls wrapped differently                           │
│ □ Same data transformation with different variable names       │
│ □ Same conditional logic serving the same purpose              │
│ □ Functions that could be unified with a parameter             │
│                                                                 │
│ Candidate duplicates:                                           │
│ - [file1:line] functionA() and [file2:line] functionB()        │
│   Similar because: [what they both do]                         │
│ - [none found]                                                  │
│                                                                 │
│ NOTE: This is distinct from:                                    │
│   - 2.5.2 (competing features — old vs new systems)            │
│   - Copy-paste duplicates (identical code in multiple places)  │
│ This section finds functions with the same INTENT but          │
│ different IMPLEMENTATION.                                       │
│                                                                 │
│ VERDICT: [CLEAN / DUPLICATES FOUND - add consolidation to plan]│
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
OVERALL HEALTH: [✅ PASS - proceed to planning / ⚠️ ISSUES - add fixes to plan]

PRE-WORK TASKS (add to plan if any):
- [ ] [Consolidate X and Y into single service]
- [ ] [Remove dead code from Z]
- [ ] [Move API key to edge function]
- [ ] [Consolidate functionA and functionB — same intent, different impl]
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
```

